  Day5MetBeforeDialog: []
  Day6Dialog:
  - "You keep asking why the trenches bend.\nBecause straight ground is where men
    die fastest.\nA wall sees farther than you think, and a cannon loves a straight
    line.\nEvery turn steals its sight.\nThat is not cleverness \u2014 it is habit
    learned from graves.\nIf you watch long enough, you will see that war is mostly
    about refusing the enemy clean answers."
  Day7FirstTimeDialog:
  - "You wonder why we do not dig under the fort.\nLook at the ground. Stone sits
    too close, and the sea waits beneath it.\nA tunnel here would speak before it
    ever worked \u2014 sound carries, water follows.\nThe Knights would hear us long
    before we reached them.\nSo we stay above, where silence can still be shaped.\nSome
    places cannot be cheated. They must be endured."
  Day7MetBeforeDialog:
  - "You wonder why we do not dig under the fort.\nLook at the ground. Stone sits
    too close, and the sea waits beneath it.\nA tunnel here would speak before it
    ever worked \u2014 sound carries, water follows.\nThe Knights would hear us long
    before we reached them.\nSo we stay above, where silence can still be shaped.\nSome
    places cannot be cheated. They must be endured."
  Day8FirstTimeDialog:
  - "You see the trench creeping forward and think it is slow.\nIt is slow on purpose.\nSpeed
    invites fire. Distance invites patience.\nEach length we gain lets the guns move
    closer without bleeding men dry.\nThe fort answers less now, not because it is
    weak, but because it is tired.\nThat is how walls begin to fail \u2014 not all
    at once, but everywhere."
  Day8MetBeforeDialog:
  - "You see the trench creeping forward and think it is slow.\nIt is slow on purpose.\nSpeed
    invites fire. Distance invites patience.\nEach length we gain lets the guns move
    closer without bleeding men dry.\nThe fort answers less now, not because it is
    weak, but because it is tired.\nThat is how walls begin to fail \u2014 not all
    at once, but everywhere."
  Day9FirstTimeDialog:
  - 'The turns are tighter today. That tells you we are close enough for stone to
    fall without warning.

    Men fear this part, because the enemy feels near.

    But
    closeness is safer than exposure.

    Straight approaches look brave. They end
    quickly.

    Corners let men live long enough to finish the work.

    Remember
    that when you hear shouting from the walls.'
  Day9MetBeforeDialog:
  - 'The turns are tighter today. That tells you we are close enough for stone to
    fall without warning.

    Men fear this part, because the enemy feels near.

    But
    closeness is safer than exposure.

    Straight approaches look brave. They end
    quickly.

    Corners let men live long enough to finish the work.

    Remember
    that when you hear shouting from the walls.'
  Day10FirstTimeDialog:
  - "Now the trench can go no farther.\nThat does not mean it has failed.\nIt has
    done what it was meant to do \u2014 carry men where they could not walk openly.\nThe
    guns will finish what earth began.\nForts do not fall because they are broken.\nThey
    fall because they are made to answer too many demands at once, until silence
    becomes easier than resistance."
  Day10MetBeforeDialog:
  - "Now the trench can go no farther.\nThat does not mean it has failed.\nIt has
    done what it was meant to do \u2014 carry men where they could not walk openly.\nThe
    guns will finish what earth began.\nForts do not fall because they are broken.\nThey
    fall because they are made to answer too many demands at once, until silence
    becomes easier than resistance."
